This is the magic line. 
It compares: "Should I add this current number (x) to my previous streak (current_max + x), or is my previous streak so deeply in the negative that I'm better off abandoning it and starting a brand new streak starting right at x?"

4. max_so_far = max(max_so_far, current_max)
We check if our newly updated running streak broke the all-time high record. If it did, we save it as the new maximum.

5. return max_so_far
Once the loop finishes checking every number, it outputs the highest sub-array sum found.



